@dev Wraps native assets and relays wrapped ERC20 tokens to the other chain.
 Call msg.sender will receive assets on the other side of the bridge.

@dev Wraps native assets and relays wrapped ERC20 tokens to the other chain.
 @param _receiver bridged assets receiver on the other side of the bridge.

@dev Ether receive function.
 Should be only called from the WETH contract when withdrawing native coins. Will revert otherwise.

devdoc.details: Omnibridge extension for processing native and wrapped native assets. Intended to work with WETH/WBNB/WXDAI tokens, see:   https://etherscan.io/address/0xc02aaa39b223fe8d0a0e5c4f27ead9083c756cc2   https://bscscan.com/address/0xbb4CdB9CBd36B01bD1cBaEBF2De08d9173bc095c   https://blockscout.com/poa/xdai/address/0xe91D153E0b41518A2Ce8Dd3D7944Fa863463a97d

claimTokens(address,address).details: Claims stuck coins/tokens. Only contract owner can call this method.

params._token: address of claimed token contract, address(0) for native coins.

params._weth: address of the WETH token used for wrapping/unwrapping native coins (e.g. WETH/WBNB/WXDAI).

onTokenBridged(address,uint256,bytes).details: Bridged callback function used for unwrapping received tokens. Can only be called by the associated Omnibridge contract.

params._data: extra data passed alongside with relayTokensAndCall on the other side of the bridge. Should contain coins receiver address.
params._token: bridged token contract address, should be WETH.

transferOwnership(address).details: Changes the owner of this contract.

wrapAndRelayTokens().details: Wraps native assets and relays wrapped ERC20 tokens to the other chain. Call msg.sender will receive assets on the other side of the bridge.

wrapAndRelayTokens(address).details: Wraps native assets and relays wrapped ERC20 tokens to the other chain.

params._receiver: bridged assets receiver on the other side of the bridge.
